summary.incident:
Dan Petrescu is forced to make a change.
Aly Abeid is not able to carry on due to
injury. He is replaced by Leonardo Bolgado
(CFR Cluj).

The teams are back out for the second half
and here is a change on the pitch. Elias
Charalambous gives a chance to Alexandru
Constantin Stoian and Mihai Toma (FCSB)
is off.

Half-time substitution. Alexandru Baluta
(FCSB) is replaced by Juri Cisotti.

Elias Charalambous makes a switch. Malcom
Edjouma is coming on in place of Marius
Stefanescu (FCSB) at the start of the second
period.

Joyskim Dawa (FCSB) comes onto the pitch
after Siyabonga Ngezana signals to the bench
that he cannot continue any longer after
picking up an injury.

Goal! Adrian Paun tees up Louis Munteanu
(CFR Cluj) inside the box, and he keeps
his cool to find the bottom right corner.
0:1.

David Miculescu (FCSB) finds some space
inside the box and scores with a terrific
header low inside the left post, giving
the goalkeeper no chance.

This yellow card was deserved. The tackle
by Juri Cisotti (FCSB) was quite harsh and
Sebastian Coltescu didn't hesitate to show
him a yellow card.

Virgiliu Postolachi comes off the pitch
to be replaced by Mohammed Kamara (CFR Cluj).

Sebastian Coltescu shows a yellow card to
Florin Tanase (FCSB) for his blatant foul.

The referee signals that it is time for
a substitution and Baba Alhassan (FCSB)
will replace Vlad Chiriches.

Florin Tanase (FCSB) makes a bad challenge
and is given a second yellow card which
means he's off.

Meriton Korenica (CFR Cluj) has tested the
patience of referee Sebastian Coltescu and
goes into the book for a previous late challenge.

The referee stops play so that a substitution
can be made and Andres Sfait (CFR Cluj)
comes onto the pitch for Adrian Paun.

Dan Petrescu has decided to introduce fresh
legs, with Kader Keita (CFR Cluj) replacing
Beni Nkololo.

Mohammed Kamara (CFR Cluj) is booked after
bringing down an opponent. Sebastian Coltescu
had an easy-decision to make.

Valentin Cretu (FCSB) receives a yellow
card for infringement.

summary.incident:
Marian Barbu shows a yellow card to Alexandru
Pantea (FCSB) for his blatant foul.

Simao Rocha sends a precise lofted cross
into the box. Louis Munteanu (CFR Cluj)
latches on to it and finishes with a quick
shot inside the right post. The goalkeeper
had no chance. The score changes to 1:0.

The game is over for William Baeten (FCSB).
Daniel Popa comes on for the second half.

Here is a change after the half-time break.
David Miculescu (FCSB) is replaced by Alexandru
Baluta.

Half-time substitution. Elias Charalambous
decided to make a change. Baba Alhassan
(FCSB) is replaced by Valentin Cretu.

Elias Charalambous has made a change at
the break. Octavian Popescu (FCSB) has come
on in place of Alexandru Pantea.

Goal! Simao Rocha puts a cross into the
box and finds Louis Munteanu (CFR Cluj),
who latches on to it and strikes the ball
into the bottom right corner. He makes it
2:0.

Goal! A mistake from the defence gifted
a chance to a lurking Alexandru Baluta (FCSB),
who keeps his cool and rolls the ball into
the net from close range. 2:1.

The referee signals a substitution. Andrei
Artean (CFR Cluj) is brought on as a substitute
for Adrian Paun.

Here comes a substitution. Ionut Pantiru
is given a rest as he is replaced by Risto
Radunovic (FCSB).

Dan Petrescu has decided to make a change.
Robert Filip replaces Louis Munteanu (CFR
Cluj).

It will be a substitution. Virgiliu Postolachi
(CFR Cluj) is ready to enter the pitch as
Alin Fica walks off.

Goal! Joyskim Dawa (FCSB) fires the rebound
into the bottom left corner after the ball
breaks to him in the box. The score is 2:2.

Dan Petrescu decides to make a substitution.
Ciprian Deac will be replaced by Meriton
Korenica (CFR Cluj).

The manager makes a subsitution with Peter
Michael (CFR Cluj) coming on for Mohammed
Kamara.

The game has begun to heat up. Robert Filip
(CFR Cluj) challenges an opponent and receives
a deserved yellow card for his ugly tackle.

This yellow card was deserved. The tackle
by Virgiliu Postolachi (CFR Cluj) was quite
harsh and Marian Barbu didn't hesitate to
show him a yellow card.
